<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1751,2029]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Head and pronotum yellow, scutellum with pale brown central area, lateral margins lemon yellow with two faint fuscous spots near base and another before apex. Forewings ivory white with dark brown mottling except lateral areas beyond well marked median spot; latter with anterior smaller and lateral large rather elongate spot, dark brown, anterior margin lacking brown mottling except a few. Legs in male pale ochraceous; in female, femora dark brown; bases of setae on tibiae in both sexes dark brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1751,2029]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,861]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis box="[199,364,1932,1957]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
<collectingCountry box="[199,257,1932,1957]" name="Malta" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Male</collectingCountry>
genitalia
</emphasis>
: Pygofer in lateral view longer than its height, posterior margin conically rounded, macrosetae confined to posterior half. Valve approximately 
<number box="[716,751,1968,1993]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as wide at base as long medially. Subgenital plates broadly rounded at base, terminal fingerlike process about 
<number box="[825,860,2004,2029]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="3.5">3.5</number>
times shorter than total length, long hairlike setae along lateral margin. Style about 
<number box="[534,569,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as wide at base, abruptly narrowed in middle; subapical lobe well developed with a few hairlike setae, apophysis directed posteriorly. Connective with stem narrow and slightly longer than arms Aedeagus with shafts elongate, tapering abruptly from posterior surface at midlength to slender anteriorly curved in apical half, gonopore on posterior and inner surface at midlength, dorsal margin of shafts serrated in middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis box="[199,391,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite 
<number box="[594,629,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as wide at base as long medially, posterior margin concave, with one 
<taxonomicName box="[198,307,367,392]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
projection on each side of median line.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,861]" box="[199,1025,404,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis box="[199,361,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">Measurements</emphasis>
: 
<collectingCountry box="[376,434,404,429]" name="Malta" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">Male</collectingCountry>
<quantity box="[440,589,404,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.175" metricValueMax="3.25" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" unit="mm" value="3.175" valueMax="3.25" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.25 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[660,823,404,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.17" metricValueMax="1.18" metricValueMin="1.16" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" unit="mm" value="1.17" valueMax="1.18" valueMin="1.16">1.16–1.18 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
