<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="108" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,620,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[322,453,621,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcuatus">
<emphasis box="[322,453,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">H. arcuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single male from 
<collectingCountry box="[898,1007,620,645]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(not examined), it is recorded here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[381,442,655,680]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">India</collectingCountry>
. It closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Knight" authorityName="Knight" box="[701,934,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concavus">
<emphasis box="[701,844,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">H. concavus</emphasis>
Knight
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Knight. The" authorityName="Knight. The" box="[997,1277,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nielsoni">
<emphasis box="[997,1124,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="108">H. nielsoni</emphasis>
Knight. The
</taxonomicName>
absence of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">a triangular</taxonomicName>
lamellate expansion on the aedeagal shafts separates it from the former species and the tapering of the aedeagal shafts at the level of the gonopore from the latter. The color of this species also varies. The specimen from Bandipur is darker with pale brownish yellow with brown mottling on the crown of the head, the pronotum and the face; the scutum and scutellum are orange brown with brown spots on the anterior margin and the lateral and apical margins ivory with brown spots along the lateral margin.
</paragraph>
